<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1155,1396]" box="[151,854,1191,1216]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<superScript attach="none" box="[151,159,1191,1205]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">b</superScript>
: All MTD/SNSD data provided by Martin Päckert (pers. comm.)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1155,1396]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<superScript attach="none" box="[151,158,1227,1241]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">c</superScript>
: 1. 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[196,442,1228,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser (2004)</bibRefCitation>
; 2. 
<bibRefCitation author="National Museum of Natural History" box="[477,946,1228,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" refId="ref15645" refString="National Museum of Natural History (2022) Division of Birds Collections database, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution. Available from: https: // collections. nmnh. si. edu / search / birds /? nb = 317790 (accessed 14 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">National Museum of Natural History (2022)</bibRefCitation>
; 3. Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle Paris (France) (2020b); 4. Patrick Bousses, pers. comm.; 5. 
<bibRefCitation author="Meise, W." box="[722,867,1264,1288]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref15236" refString="Meise, W. (1929) Verzeichnis der Typen des Staatlichen Museums fur Tierkunde in Dresden. 2. Teil, Vogel I. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Ethnographischen Museums zu Dresden, 17 (4), 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1929">Meise (1929)</bibRefCitation>
; 6. Markus Unsöld, pers. comm.; 7. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="191 - 216" refId="ref15891" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1887) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. II. Theil. Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 2 (3), 191 - 216." type="journal article" year="1887">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz (1887)</bibRefCitation>
; 8. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H." box="[263,428,1300,1324]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="63 - 73" refId="ref16437" refString="Schifter, H. (1990) Dr. Adolf Bernhard Meyer und die Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 46 (3), 63 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">Schifter (1990)</bibRefCitation>
; 9. Hans-Martin Berg, pers. comm.; 10. Current publication.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1155,1396]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<superScript attach="left" box="[151,159,1335,1349]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">d</superScript>
Time of exchange not noted in the MTD/SNSD catalogues, but as this specimen is not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Meise, W." box="[1229,1372,1336,1360]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref15236" refString="Meise, W. (1929) Verzeichnis der Typen des Staatlichen Museums fur Tierkunde in Dresden. 2. Teil, Vogel I. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Ethnographischen Museums zu Dresden, 17 (4), 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1929">Meise (1929)</bibRefCitation>
it had most likely been removed from the MTD collection before 1929.
</paragraph>
</tableNote>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1442,1685]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
While 
<bibRefCitation author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[274,533,1442,1469]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser (2004)</bibRefCitation>
further noted that nothing was known about the remaining type specimens, there are apparently also 
<specimenCount box="[368,593,1478,1504]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">three paralectotypes</specimenCount>
in NHMW (NMW 
<geoCoordinate box="[813,891,1478,1505]" degrees="51.617" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" precision="55" value="51.617">51.617</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[891,985,1478,1505]" degrees="51.619" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" precision="55" value="-51.619">–51.619</geoCoordinate>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[995,1257,1478,1505]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="191 - 216" refId="ref15891" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1887) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. II. Theil. Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 2 (3), 191 - 216." type="journal article" year="1887">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz 1887</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schifter, H." box="[1269,1424,1478,1505]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="63 - 73" refId="ref16437" refString="Schifter, H. (1990) Dr. Adolf Bernhard Meyer und die Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 46 (3), 63 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">Schifter 1990</bibRefCitation>
), obtained through Meyer in 1884 (Hans-Martin Berg, pers. comm.). As for the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1850" box="[1068,1191,1515,1541]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Geoffroyus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1191,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Geoffroyus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens discussed above, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[235,521,1550,1577]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" pagination="191 - 216" refId="ref15891" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1887) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. II. Theil. Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 2 (3), 191 - 216." type="journal article" year="1887">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz (1887)</bibRefCitation>
described them as 
<emphasis box="[746,1036,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">‘authentische Exemplare’</emphasis>
but they are noted as 
<emphasis box="[1296,1362,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">‘type’</emphasis>
in the acquisition catalogue (Hans-Martin Berg, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1442,1685]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="NHMO" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paralectotype">
Based on information on the label and in the accompanying letter from Meyer, we conclude that the 
<collectionCode box="[1351,1437,1623,1649]" country="Norway" name="Natural History Museum, University of Oslo" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" type="Museum">NHMO</collectionCode>
specimen should be considered one of the 
<typeStatus box="[626,788,1658,1684]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
of this taxon
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
